body:
This logic isn't very simple or an established pattern: we should have more test coverage for it.

One way to organize some interesting test cases:

```typescript

describe("SharedTree", () => {
	describe("schema index summarization", () => {
		describe("incrementally reuses previous blobs", () => {
			it("on a client which never uploaded a blob");
			it("on a client which uploaded a blob")
			// this concern is orthogonal to the two above, but important
			it("if there are changes unrelated to schemaIndex");
		});

		describe("uploads new schema data", () => {
			it("without incremental summary context");
			it("when it has changed since the last summary");
		});
	});
})
```

